# Real-Time Visitor Monitoring and Automation System using LPC1768 with Integrated UART Communication

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project implements a **real-time visitor monitoring and automation system** on the **LPC1768 ARM Cortex-M3 microcontroller**.  
It combines hardware and firmware solutions to provide automated visitor tracking, data logging, and gate control.

The system uses:
- **UART communication** for serial monitoring and debugging.
- **IR sensors** to detect entry and exit events.
- **PWM-controlled servo motor** for automated gate operation.
- **RTC (Real-Time Clock)** for accurate visitor time-stamping.
- **IÂ²C-based EEPROM** for reliable visitor data storage.
- **Menu-driven interface** for system control and monitoring.

